HEADWORD: Semichorus
<hw>Sem"i*cho`rus</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A half
chorus; a passage to be sung by a selected portion of the voices, as the
female voices only, in contrast with the full choir.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semi-Christianized</ent>⟦br⟧
